## Skill & Agent Usage in Claude / Claude Code CLI

### 1. `/proofread` — Proofreading Documents

```bash
# Single file
@skills/proofread.md and @agents/proofreader.md, use the skill and agent to proofread "papers/***.docx"

# Batch process all files
/proofread all

### 2. `/review-paper` — Manuscript / Paper Review
# Review a specific manuscript
@skills/review-paper.md, use the skill to reviw papers/my_paper.docx

# Review LaTeX or PDF
/review-paper papers/research_note.tex

### 3. ` /lit-review ` — Literature Search and Synthesis
# Review a research topic
@skills//lit-review.md, use the skill to review the topic "climate risk and corporate finance"

# Use a specific paper title or research question
@skills//lit-review.md, use the skill to review the papers/ "Fama-French 3-factor model"

### 4. ` /create-slides`  — Slide Creation Workflow
# Create slides for a topic
@skills/create-slides.md, use this skill to create slides for "Climate Risk Lecture"

# Use a source paper as input
@skills/create-slides.md, use this skill to create slides for "papers/***.docx"

